## \uc0\u55357 \u56960  Overview\
\
**TUni-GPS** is a structural physics system for reconstructing space-time events under real-world distortion conditions.  \
It extends the classic GPS principle with:\
\
- TUni-Time reconstruction (absolute instead of relative)\
- Distortion analysis (gravity, Doppler, plasma)\
- Third Observer (self-analysis of measurement distortion)\
- Master formula of Action: **S = E \'d7 T_uni**\
\
---\
\
## \uc0\u55358 \u56800  Background: The TUni Principles\
\
### \uc0\u55357 \u56633  TUni-Time\
\
> TUni-Time is the reconstructed proper time of an event\'97  \
> corrected for signal delays, motion effects, and gravitational influences.  \
> It describes **not when you measure something**, but **when it actually happened.**\
\
### \uc0\u55357 \u56633  The Master Formula: `S = E \'d7 T_uni`\
\
> The Action (S) of an event is the product of its Energy `E`  \
> and the duration in which that energy acted undisturbed\'97`T_uni`.\
\
---\
\
## \uc0\u55357 \u57072 \u65039  Architecture\
\
### \uc0\u55358 \u56809  TUniEvent\
- Encapsulates the energy source of an event (e.g., 42.0 J)\
\
### \uc0\u55358 \u56809  TUniSat\
- A single "observer" featuring:\
  - Separate distortion analysis for time and space\
  - Reconstruction of position & time\
  - Observer analysis for self-assessment (Third Observer)\
\
### \uc0\u55358 \u56809  TUniSystem\
- Combines multiple `TUniSat` instances\
- Calculates **weighted averages** based on the distortion difference\
- Returns a consolidated space-time point\
\
